11:
Your laughter... You are laughing
much more now.
18:
Mertina found many of them
clustered in one place. They also
taste better when we eat them
together!
20:
O-our deepest apologies. Were we
causing too much noise?
24:
Let me... hear you. Let me know what
humans speak of.
36: My apologies. I was... lost in thought.
40:
With weather like this, nobody would
blame you for dozing off.
43:
...Is it okay for us to be here too,
though?
46:
It is. I asked those three if there was
anything else they might like...
48:
A picnic with everyone... Is what they
asked for. It was also their desire to
prepare the food.
53:
What a modest request... I suppose
those three truly enjoy doing things
for you.
56:
So it would seem. It seems they even
want to work to pay for my food
expenses.
59:
...However, I believe they are too
concerned with pleasing me.
61:
I wish they would... exercise their free
willâ€”
68: Foul dragon! Get away from her!
78:
...So you're saying that you heard a
rumor that Mertina was seen in
Palpebra, and have been searching
for her ever since?
81:
...I didn't believe it at first. She and
the others were offered as sacrifices
to the dragon, after all...
83:
Mertina... and you two, as well. Come
with me back to the village.
86:
...You drove them away so long
ago... And only now have you come
to plead your case?
89:
...I've been regretting it all along.
How I couldn't save you back then.
91:
The people in the village feel the
same. Things have calmed down a
lot since the dragon left...
93:
...Let's go home, Mertina. Even if
someone says something, I'llâ€”
95:
I... I won't go back. I'm with Lord
Schult now!
101:
...Y-you don't mean that. Come on!
This is a chance at a normal life! You
want to live with a DRAGON
instead?! Ridiculous!
103:
I'll do everything I can to help you.
You don't need to hesitate anymoreâ€”
106:
...When you brought her to me. Her
body was shaking... Her eyes... were
filled with tears.
110:
Leave us be for now. This will... take
some time.
113:
...I-I'm not giving up. I won't let
anyone ever hurt you again, Mertina!
117:
...The Guild confirmed it. The
villagers indeed have calmed down
since they stopped seeing Schult.
119:
At the very least, they shouldn't
force you out again if you return,
but...
123:
...In this situation... What is best for a
human to do?
131: What do you think is best, Schult?
136:
...I am not certain a correct answer
exists.
144:
...Our sincere apologies, Lord Schult.
We've caused you no end of trouble
today...
146:
This isn't the time to apologize,
Mertina! That stupid guy's the one to
blame, showing up and saying a
bunch of selfish garbage!
148:
...What did you think of that man,
Lord Schult?
151:
...It is hard to say. I do not know him
well.
153:
However... I do believe I know you
three well.
156:
Mertina... You are very conscious
and considerate of those around
you.
159:
...However, when you sleep, you tend
to cuddle up closely to the others
under my wings... Much like a small
child who cries out to be comforted.
162:
Aileen... You are more mature than
the others. However, you take large
bites when you eat, and your cheeks
puff up much like a child, as well.
167:
And Lucia. I wouldn't have expected
it... But you are the proudest of the
three... You know how to speak your
mind.
169:
I once told you that an iron hoe
would suffice. However, you insisted
on finding something stronger to
scratch my back with, and
embarked on an extensive search.
172:
B-but that's just because I knew we
needed to find something better!
175:
Seeing your eyes... Hearing your
voices... It has all made me wish to
understand humans better.
178:
Now, I understand what it means to
be happy from a human
perspective... And I have you three
to thank.
181:
You needn't return to the village...
And you needn't be chained to me,
either.
183:
I wish for you three to... exercise your
free will, so that you may find
greater happiness.
186:
All I want is for you three to know
true joy.
191:
W-we are honored to hear such
words from you, Lord Schult... And...
193:
...Thank you very much. We will
spend some time thinking over what
to do next...
195:
...But just for today, won't you spoil
us a little longer?
